text:
I was looking to find something better than an HP piece of junk printer that left blank lines with new ink cartridges, even after "cleaning" and the HP could not handle heavier photo paper (HP is not what it used to be), and decided to go for one of the other big names who have been around printing and imaging for a long time. Even though the Canon I settled on is considered a lower end model, B&H had it and a few other potential candidates in stock with expedited shipping;
Their potential competitors? I did not even look at one store due to bad customer service (Best Buy), and they would not have had this particular printer in their stores. The other online retailer I looked at did not have anything able to handle larger papers without moving to an expensive wide carriage plotter, and their selection was limited in the area of printers suitable for photography.
If at some point I need to "move up" from this printer, I'll be back. When I get a darkroom set up again, I will be back.
